data.name: label_instructions.Text
data.value: 1. Run the trainer program before or after running TEKKEN 7. 2. Let it show that it has attached successfully. 3. After that, simply select any one of the boss characters to access them. 3.1. Select Kazumi with Preset 7 to load Devil Kazumi 3.2. Select Heihachi with Preset 8 to load Ascended Heihachi 3.3. Select Akuma with Preset 5 to load Shin Akuma 3.4 Select Kazuya with Preset 8 to load Devil Kazuya 3.5 No Costume fix for Jin. 4. Game will automatically load the boss costume 4.1 If "Moveset Depends on Costume" box is checked. 4.2 Uncheck it to make boss moves load on any costume 5. Upon success, the checkbox below character names will become marked. 6. Press the "Update" button to update address & requirement files.

data.name: label_kazuya.Text

data.name: label_heihachi.Text
data.value: ASCENDED HEIHACHI: 1. 1, 1, 2: last hit damage, recovery and reaction changed 2. 1, 2, 2: last hit damage, recovery and reaction changed (screw attack) 3. standing 4: revorery and reaction changed (now a screw attack) 4. b + 4: pushback changed on standing/crouching opponent 5. 3, 4: last hit damage, recovery and reaction changed 6. d/f + 1, 1 + 2: Twin Pistons, -27 on block 7. CD + 2 (hold d/f): Delayed Wind God Fist (acts like a EWGF) 8. d + 2 + 3: Completey changed 9. 3 + 4: Armoured Raijin Stance available 10. Spinning Demon: kicks increased upto 6, properties changed 11. d + 1 + 2: Ultimate Rage Art 12. Rage Art button: Regular Rage Art 13. Idle Stance: Added Eletric VFX 14. Special Intro/Outro

data.name: label_akuma.Text
data.value:
SHIN AKUMA: 1. d + 3 + 4: Ashura Wen - Meter Recharge move

data.name: label_jin.Text
data.value:

2. d + 1 + 2 - Zenshin stance changed (Input also 1+2+3 OR 1+2+4) Built-in sidestep to the right Follow-up 1, 2 gets removed
